    	<li id="comment-17331" class="comment c5 c-y2011 c-m01 c-d03 c-h22 depth-1">
    		    		<div class="comment-author vcard"><img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/c4616a41ee8891b51b1f15243ac399b9?s=80&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D80&amp;r=G' class='photo avatar avatar-80 photo' height='80' width='80' /> <span class="fn n">jony Sonic</span></div>
    		<div class="comment-meta">Posted 3 Jan ’11 at 21:26 <span class="meta-sep">|</span> <a href="#comment-17331" title="Permalink to this comment">Permalink</a></div>
                <div class="comment-content">
        		<p>The original TRON suits weren&#8217;t active light suits, the look was achieved by  retro-reflective tape and camera lights applied to Lisberger&#8217;s remarkable and labor-intensive  frame-by-frame HC matte system and painstaking planning and rotoscope work, much like ILM&#8217;s light-sabre work but incredibly more troublesome and detailed.</p>
    		</div>
			<div class="comment-reply-link"><a class='comment-reply-link' href='/tron-legacy-light-suit-costume/15850/?replytocom=17331#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-17331", "17331", "respond", "15850")'>Reply</a></div>			<ul class='children'>
